{
  "stem": "27335.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then not to grow up in the Catholic Church, in the Catholic faith, uh, well, he was-- he was 90% atheist.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He attended the church once a year, just for the sake of [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then, uh, agreed with my mother and my mother [? the girls, ?] so he agreed that-- he placed me into the, for my second grade, into the Calvinist church.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My little sister, who was just-- she stayed alive in [INAUDIBLE], she is only 18 months younger than I am.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I was-- I was in grade two, she was in great first in the Calvinist church.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that's where I finished my, oh, the six years.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, then, but my father could afford it-- well, I emphasize could afford it, because very few people in those days, even to send their children into high school.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But my father, being a harness maker, in the whole-- whole district there, he was the only harness maker.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And being an upholsterer, working for the-- for the higher class, you see, so he had a little money, so he could send me to high school in the provincial capital, in [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the year after that, also my sister.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were commuting from the-- from the village to the-- for four years, every morning, between the school.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The school term, we woke up to 5 o'clock every morning, because the train was leaving at 6.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the high schools, those days-- any kind of high schools, the my kind of, and the gymnasium-- what, the gymnasium, as they called it.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My sister went to-- and trade schools, and commercial schools-- were only lasted till 1 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then the train was coming, we always had to run to catch the train.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
